  "title": "Customer Relation Officer (Construction, Engineering)",
  "description": "<p><ul><li><p>Manage and resolve feedback, complaints, and disputes related to construction activities in a timely and professional manner.</p></li><li><p>Plan, coordinate, and implement public relations initiatives, including the preparation and distribution of circulars, notices, and official correspondence to the public, residents, and tenants.</p></li><li><p>Attend and participate in dialogue sessions with Clients, Residents’ Committees, Town Councils, and other relevant stakeholders as directed.</p></li><li><p>Provide administrative and logistical support for Construction Working Committee meetings and other project-related meetings when required.</p></li><li><p>Conduct regular site visits to residents and tenants affected by construction works to gather feedback and keep them informed of work schedules, changes, and potential impacts.</p></li><li><p>Work closely with contractors and project teams to proactively mitigate issues and complaints arising from construction activities.</p></li><li><p>Build and maintain positive working relationships with residents, tenants, and key stakeholders.</p></li><li><p>Participate in project meetings and accurately record minutes related to assigned projects.</p></li><li><p>Maintain proper documentation and records of all public relations cases, correspondence, and communication materials.</p></li></ul></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Diploma in any related fields.</p></li><li><p>Minimum 2 years of customer relations experience in Construction Industry</p></li><li><p>Good communication skill</p></li></ul><p>Interested applicants for the above advertised position(s), please kindly email an updated copy of your resume to: <a href=\"mailto:gs1@talenttradersg.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">gs1@talenttradersg.com</a><br /></p><p>EA License No.: 13C6305</p><p>Registration No.: R1985956 (VIVIEN TAN)</p><p>For candidate who applied for the advertised position is deemed to have consented to us that we may collect, use or disclose your personal information for purpose in connection with the services provided by us.</p>",
